oai_dc:dc.dc:title: DETERMINATION OF CROSS SECTIONS FOR GRAVITY TYPE QUAY WALLS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Yuksel, Tugce
Yuksel, Yalcin
Basaran, Busra
Cevik, Esin
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Block type structure
quay wall
seismic behavior
shaking tank
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Block type quay walls are widely used as port structures in the world. In this study three types of vertical block type quay walls with different block size exposed to seismic loading were investigated experimentally. The block ratios of Type I, Type II and III vertical wall models are B/h=2, 1.5 and 1.5 & H/h=6, 6 and 3, respectively. The tests were conducted in the shaking tank with different harmonic seismic loadings and the behaviors of these walls were investigated comparatively.
